This paper discusses the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) in robotics applications, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). However, the paper also focuses on the limitations of DRL and proposes an interactive learning approach that involves human corrective feedback, which is related to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning for policy shaping, which is related to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed approach in terms of reducing human training effort, which is related to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, and cs.CV, in that order.
